{
    "level": "B1",
    "intro": "In this topic, you will learn to form <strong>passive with prepositional verbs</strong>: look after, speak to, pay for and others. The main rule: <strong>the preposition remains with the verb</strong>.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Active",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "Active state with a preposition:",
            "example": "Someone looked after the children."
        },
        {
            "label": "Passive",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "The passive preposition remains:",
            "example": "The children were looked after."
        },
        {
            "label": "Rule",
            "color": "rose",
            "text": "<strong>V + preposition</strong> → <strong>be + V3 + preposition</strong>",
            "example": "speak to → be spoken to"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. How to form Prepositional Passive",
    "intro": "The passive form with prepositional verbs:",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Formula",
            "title": "be + V3 + preposition",
            "subtitle": "The preposition always remains at the end"
        },
        {
            "label": "Example",
            "title": "look after → be looked after",
            "subtitle": "She was looked after by her grandmother."
        },
        {
            "label": "Don't change",
            "title": "The preposition does not move",
            "subtitle": "❌ After her was looked (wrong)"
        },
        {
            "label": "Agent",
            "title": "You can add \"by\"",
            "subtitle": "She was spoken to by the manager."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Typical prepositional verbs",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "look after / look at",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "<strong>look after</strong> - to look after. <strong>look at</strong> - look at.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Active: Someone looks after the children.",
                    "ua": "Active: Someone looks after the children."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: The children are looked after.",
                    "ua": "Passive: The children are looked after."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Active: Everyone looked at him.",
                    "ua": "Active: Everyone looked at him."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: He was looked at by everyone.",
                    "ua": "Passive: He was looked at by everyone."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "speak to / talk about",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "<strong>speak to</strong> — talk with. <strong>talk about</strong> - talk about.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Active: The manager spoke to her.",
                    "ua": "Active: The manager spoke to her."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: She was spoken to by the manager.",
                    "ua": "Passive: She was spoken to by the manager."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Active: Everyone talks about this issue.",
                    "ua": "Active: Everyone talks about this issue."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: This issue is talked about a lot.",
                    "ua": "Passive: This issue is talked about a lot."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "pay for / account for",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "<strong>pay for</strong> — to pay for. <strong>account for</strong> — to explain.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Active: The company paid for the training.",
                    "ua": "Active: The company paid for the training."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: The training was paid for.",
                    "ua": "Passive: The training was paid for."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Active: This accounts for 50% of sales.",
                    "ua": "Active: This accounts for 50% of sales."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: 50% of sales is accounted for by this.",
                    "ua": "Passive: 50% of sales is accounted for by this."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "laugh at / shout at",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "<strong>laugh at</strong> - to laugh at. <strong>shout at</strong> - shout at.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Active: They laughed at his joke.",
                    "ua": "Active: They laughed at his joke."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: His joke was laughed at.",
                    "ua": "Passive: His joke was laughed at."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Active: The boss shouted at him.",
                    "ua": "Active: The boss shouted at him."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: He was shouted at by the boss.",
                    "ua": "Passive: He was shouted at by the boss."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Phrasal verbs in the passive",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Phrasal verbs",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "<strong>Phrasal verbs</strong> with prepositions/participles also form the passive.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Active: They called off the meeting.",
                    "ua": "Active: They called off the meeting."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: The meeting was called off.",
                    "ua": "Passive: The meeting was called off."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Active: Someone broke into the house.",
                    "ua": "Active: Someone broke into the house."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: The house was broken into.",
                    "ua": "Passive: The house was broken into."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "put off / turn down",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "<strong>put off</strong> — postpone. <strong>turn down</strong> - reject.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Active: They put off the decision.",
                    "ua": "Active: They put off the decision."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: The decision was put off.",
                    "ua": "Passive: The decision was put off."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Active: They turned down my application.",
                    "ua": "Active: They turned down my application."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: My application was turned down.",
                    "ua": "Passive: My application was turned down."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "bring up / take care of",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "<strong>bring up</strong> - to bring up. <strong>take care of</strong> — to take care.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Active: Her grandmother brought her up.",
                    "ua": "Active: Her grandmother brought her up."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: She was brought up by her grandmother.",
                    "ua": "Passive: She was brought up by her grandmother."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Active: Someone took care of the problem.",
                    "ua": "Active: Someone took care of the problem."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Passive: The problem was taken care of.",
                    "ua": "Passive: The problem was taken care of."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. Summary: Active → Passive",
    "intro": "Transformation of prepositional verbs:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "look after",
            "ua": "look after",
            "note": "The baby was looked after."
        },
        {
            "en": "speak to",
            "ua": "speak to",
            "note": "She was spoken to."
        },
        {
            "en": "pay for",
            "ua": "pay for",
            "note": "The meal was paid for."
        },
        {
            "en": "laugh at",
            "ua": "laugh at",
            "note": "He was laughed at."
        },
        {
            "en": "deal with",
            "ua": "deal with",
            "note": "The issue was dealt with."
        },
        {
            "en": "refer to",
            "ua": "refer to",
            "note": "This book is often referred to."
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 <strong>The preposition always remains at the end of the sentence!</strong>"
}

{
    "title": "5. Typical mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Error 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Skipping the preposition.",
            "wrong": "The children were looked.",
            "right": "✅ The children were looked after."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Preposition at the beginning.",
            "wrong": "After the children was looked.",
            "right": "✅ The children were looked after."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Change of preposition.",
            "wrong": "She was spoken with.",
            "right": "✅ She was spoken to."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 4",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Omission of a particle in a phrasal verb.",
            "wrong": "The meeting was called.",
            "right": "✅ The meeting was called off."
        }
    ]
}
